# Flyers Unit Authoring (U2–U12)

**Read first:** `scripts/lib/flyers-blueprints/TEMPLATE.md`

**Gold reference (Unit 1):** `scripts/lib/flyers-blueprints/unit-01/` + `shared/family-and-friends-extended-content.mjs`

**Curriculum:** `data/curriculum/cambridge-curriculum-map.json` → `levels.flyers.units[N-1]`

## When user asks to create Flyers U2–U12

1. Read unit brief from curriculum map.
2. Copy **structure** from Flyers Unit 1 — never copy Family and Friends **content**.
3. Create `shared/<slug>-content.mjs` + `unit-0N.mjs` + `unit-0N/*.mjs`.
4. Target: **18 lessons × 90 exercises** (Learn, Practice, Check, Apply, Review).
5. Character **Minh (11, Hanoi)** across Flyers units.
6. Only **Check** uses AI `writing` / `speaking`.
7. Flyers: `minWords` 25, speaking `maxDurationSeconds` 120, `levelTag: "flyers"`.
8. All explanations in **Vietnamese**.
9. **No image-based questions** — use `sceneDescription` (text) only; see `unit-content-authoring.mdc`.

## Pipeline

```bash
node scripts/generate-cambridge-units.mjs flyers <N>
npm run validate:flyers
npm run generate:listening-audio -- flyers <N>
npm run seed:flyers -- --from <N> --to <N> --unlock-test-student
```

## Scope

- **In scope:** Flyers units 2–12
- **Out of scope:** Movers, Starters, KET, PET — separate blueprint folders

See: `.cursor/rules/unit-content-authoring.mdc`
